events.text: [color=#ffed29](Alright, now that [tootroot] is taken care of, I gotta get ready too.)

[color=#ffed29](I might need to get another job while I’m waiting for them to get back to me.)
[i]sigh
[color=#ffed29](I'll need to ask good questions tomorrow.)

Oh my gods! Look at the lettuce head on this tootroot!
She looks incredible!
What a lovely shade of green you got!
I’m so proud of you. [tootroot], you’ve grown so much!

[i]Lettuce[/i] celebrate with more lettuce!
And I’ll get a cool bath!

[tootroot]! Oh my gods!
The peaches on you are HUGE! Are you gonna topple over???
[i]Haha[/i], I guess not! You’re perfectly balanced.
[i]Haha[/i], I see the need for a WHOLE tree now. You gotta support these giants!
I’m sure you’re tired, so I’ll get you more peaches, and I’ll get a cool bath going, too.
What a BOUNTY of tomatoes! And they all look so full and ripe!
You look adorable, I love this pop of color on you.
Come inside! I’ll get you some more tomatoes and I’ll draw a cool bath for you.

Do you want more food or another bath?
Maybe more pets!

And I don’t really know what that means, or what’s going to happen after.
So, I’m nervous.
Like, I’m definitely happy that I’m not fired, but still… not having income is going to be tough.
Also, assuming I get to keep the apartment, which is a huge “IF.”
Do you want me to try your crop?
Let’s see how amazing it is!
[tootroot], this is incredible! It’s beyond fresh!

And I feel so energized!
Now I see why apothecaries use your crops so much for their medicines.

You’re so cool.
Thanks for making me feel better, [tootroot].
Look at you! Wow, one day and you’re halfway bloomed.
You gained a couple inches on you!

Come in!
I’ll get you some more lettuce, and I’ll get a cool bath going too!
Excuse me, miss, what are you doing back…
[i]Haha[/i], I guess that makes sense if you’re going to grow a peach. But I can’t believe this was done in one day!
You’re going to need good food and a nice bath to support that ecosystem you got on your back!
I’m so glad you came back to visit!
Dang, you must’ve been sprouting a new leaf every couple hours.
It’s paying off, you look great. You’re so leafy!

But come in, come in!
I’ll get you some more tomatoes, draw a cool bath, and I’ll be sure to get some good scratches in, too.
What am I going to do…

I hope getting furloughed means I get to keep the apartment.
I mean, it’s not like they’ll hire a new person, right?
So, there’s no harm in letting me stay, right?
Yeah, you’re right. Even if I do stay, I’ll need some way of paying off bills.
Maybe Rondeau needs help at ABP?
Maybe one of the cafes is hiring?

[i]sigh
Well, let’s hope that the “gift” they’re giving me tomorrow can cover me until I start making money again.
Well, I gotta get ready for work. Come back tomorrow?
[color=#ffed29](Alright, now that [tootroot] is taken care of, I gotta get ready too.)

[color=#ffed29](I might need to get another job while I’m waiting for them to get back to me.)
[i]sigh
[color=#ffed29](I'll need to ask good questions tomorrow.)

events.question: Nothing, man…except for you being suspended!!! Dude, I can’t believe it.

events.text: Management just gets to do whatever they want, and I just have to take it.

events.choice: But what can I do, right?

events.text: I can’t believe it, either...but what can I do about it, right?

I guess...
But, how does THIS help morale?
It’s like they’re picking on the newest guy…
I mean, it makes sense—it would be weird to pick on someone more senior.
What am I going to do without you, man??

Herb, you’re friends with everyone at work, you’ll be fine!!
You don’t have to sit outside with me anymore, you can be in the lounge with everyone.
But, I’ve come to like those stairs…

It’s [i]our[/i] stairs, you can’t sit there without me.
You gotta go back, join the boys at lunch!

It would feel weird without you…
I remember I almost took you out with the door that first day.
Yeah, you almost killed my lunch!

[i]Haha[/i], now I do.
But for the company, not for the step.
I just like looking at the city.
We gotta hang at the Tavern.

Okay…I just wanted to make sure we would still hang.
And check how you were doing.

Yeah...
Hey, if they’re hiring at the Tavern, then you’ll see me for sure!
Oh, right! You could chef it up there!

That would be sick, I’d have someone to give me stuff on the house!
Maybe this is for the best…

[i]Haha[/i]! I’m joking, I’m joking.
Okay, glad to hear you’re okay…
I’ll see you soon?
I have to go in to pick up their "furlough gift."
[color=#ffed29](So lucky to have Herb as a friend.)
[color=#ffed29](I guess I get ready for bed and ready to start my furlough period.)
